Decentralized Knowledge Graph L1
Overview

Decentralized Knowledge Graph L1 is designed to store, validate, and interconnect structured knowledge across decentralized networks.

Features

Verifiable knowledge nodes

Graph-based data relationships

Collaborative knowledge curation

Immutable knowledge provenance

API access for AI applications

Architecture
Knowledge Registry

Stores nodes and semantic relationships.

Validation Layer

Ensures data integrity through consensus.

Query Engine

Allows graph-based data queries.

AI Integration Layer

Supports machine learning data pipelines.

Use Cases

AI knowledge datasets

Research collaboration

Decentralized Wikipedia-style platforms

Semantic data networks

5. Tokenized Carbon Credit L1
Overview

Tokenized Carbon Credit L1 enables transparent issuance, tracking, and trading of carbon credits using blockchain technology.

Features

Verifiable carbon credit tokens

Transparent emissions tracking

Automated carbon offset markets

Compliance reporting tools

Cross-market interoperability

Architecture
Carbon Asset Registry

Stores verified environmental assets.

Tokenization Engine

Converts credits into tradable tokens.

Market Settlement Layer

Handles trading and settlement.

Compliance Module

Tracks regulatory reporting.

Use Cases

Corporate carbon offsetting

Environmental trading markets

Sustainability reporting

Climate impact transparency
